race.description: Keeneland November Breeding Stock Sale Handicap
race.comment: ALADDIN'S GIRL (8) has settled worse than midfield then worked home well to just miss the placings at her two runs to date, the latest over this distance at Kembla. Both performances have been good enough to put her on top in a modest line-up. AUGUSTA NATIONAL (2) went back from a wide gate then closed hard to get up for third on debut over 1200m at Newcastle last time out. Draws a nice gate and the blinkers go on so he might be up in the leading division this time. Hard to hold out over the extra furlong. CHICAMA (1) was wide for the trip so his effort to finish third when resuming over 1200m at Rosehill was impressive. Consistent colt who is sure to be thereabouts again. BARKING MAD (6) was only fair first-up at Kembla but started favourite that day so deserves another chance. CLANWILLIAM (5) caught the eye on debut at Rosehill a fortnight ago. Should be hard to hold out over the extra 200m.
